FDA - Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS) 
FOIA Case Report Information
Update 04 Feb 2015: The neurologist spontaneously reported via a Biogen Idec Area Business Manager (ABM) 
that the patient was hospitalized (dates of hospitalization not provided) for pseudomonas aeruginosa infection 
(onset unknown; previously reported as respiratory infection caused by pseudomonas). During the admission, the 
patient had a bronchoaspiration (onset unknown). Testing and treatment for the events was not provided. The 
event of respiratory infection caused by pseudomonas is ongoing. The outcome of the event bronchoaspiration is 
unknown. Causality for the events was not assessed by the neurologist. 
Update 10 Feb 2015: The neurologist spontaneously reported that the patient had not recovered from the 
respiratory infection caused by pseudomonas. The neurologist also indicated that the neurological situation of the 
patient had deteriorated, although the last MRI performed (date unknown; presume reference to the MRI performed
17 Jan 2015) did not show differences compared to the previous ones.
Update 11 Feb 2015: The neurologist spontaneously reported that the patient passed away on (b) (6)  The 
cause of death was not provided. Testing and treatment were not provided. It is unknown if an autopsy was 
performed. Causality for the event of death was not assessed by the neurologist.
Update 12 Feb 2015: The neurologist spontaneously reported that he thinks the patient died due to the PML and 
the pseudomonas infection. No autopsy will be performed.
Update 23 Feb 2015: The neurologist provided MRI images from the following dates: 26 May 2014 (presume 
reference to previously reported 28 May 2014 MRI), 09 Dec 2014, 11 Dec 2014, 02 Jan 2015, and 19 Jan 2015 
(presume reference to previously reported 17 Jan 2015 MRI). No corresponding results were provided.
Update 03 Mar 2015: On 03 Mar 2015, Biogen Idec considers this case confirmed for PML based on positive CSF, 
consistent radiological evidence, and clinical symptoms.